President Obama addressed the U.N. Peacekeeping Summit, highlighting the importance of peacekeeping operations in maintaining international peace and security. He acknowledged the challenges faced by peacekeepers, including new conflicts, terrorism, and the refugee crisis. The President pledged additional support from the United States, including expanding military officers serving in peacekeeping operations and offering logistical support. He emphasized the need for more nations to contribute forces and improve the protection of civilians. President Obama also called for reforms and modernization of peace operations, as well as increased support for U.N. diplomatic tools to prevent conflicts. He concluded by expressing confidence that with the necessary support and reforms, peace operations can be strengthened for the future.